# Funcin para plotear el history mediante loss_value o accuracy respecto a el numero de epocas
def show_history(history, metrics=['accuracy']):
    """
    Visualize history
    :param history:
    :return:
    """

    # Plot history: Loss
    plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
    plt.title('Loss history')
    plt.ylabel('Loss value')
    plt.xlabel('No. epoch')
    plt.legend(['train', 'validation'], loc='upper left')
    plt.show()

    for metric in metrics:
        # Plot history:
        plt.plot(history.history[metric])
        plt.plot(history.history['val_' + metric])
        plt.title(metric + ' history')
        plt.ylabel(metric + ' value (%)')
        plt.xlabel('No. epoch')
        plt.legend(['train', 'validation'], loc='upper left')
        plt.show()

# capas de la red
input = Input(shape=(32,32,3))
input_flat = layers.Flatten()(input)
layer = layers.Dense(units=1000, activation='sigmoid')(input_flat)
layer = layers.Dense(units=500, activation='sigmoid')(layer)
layer = layers.Dense(units=200, activation='sigmoid')(layer)
output = layers.Dense(units=100, activation='softmax')(layer)

# creamos el modelo
model = Model(inputs=input, outputs=output)
print(model.summary())

# optimizador
optimizer = SGD(learning_rate=0.01)

# funcin loss
loss = SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=False)

# mtrica
metrics = ['accuracy']

# compilamos el modelo
model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss=loss, metrics=metrics)

input = Input(shape=(32,32,3))
conv=Conv2D(10,(3,3),1,padding='same',activation='relu')(input)
#conv=BatchNormalization()(conv)
conv=Conv2D(20,(3,3),1,padding='same',activation='relu')(conv)

conv=MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2, strides=2)(conv)

conv=Dropout(.50)(conv)
conv=BatchNormalization()(conv)


conv=Flatten()(conv)
conv=Dropout(.5)(conv)
layer=layers.Dense(1000,activation='relu')(conv)

layer=Dropout(.5)(layer)
output=layers.Dense(100,activation='softmax')(layer)

# creamos el modelo
model_5 = Model(inputs=input, outputs=output)
print(model_5.summary())

# funcin loss

# mtrica
metrics = ['accuracy']
model_5._name='model_5'
# compilamos el modelo

# capas de la red
F = np.arange(1000,2500,150) 
res = 40
list_val_accuracy = []
for initial_unit in F:

  # print(f'Training substracting: {res}')
  print(f'Training with these units:{initial_unit}, {initial_unit-res}, {initial_unit-(res*2)},  {initial_unit-(res*3)}')
  input = Input(shape=(32,32,3))
  input_flat = layers.Flatten()(input)
  layer = layers.Dense(units=initial_unit, activation='relu')(input_flat)
  layer = layers.Dense(units=initial_unit-res, activation='relu')(layer)
  layer = layers.Dense(units=initial_unit-(res*2), activation='relu')(layer)
  layer = layers.Dense(units=initial_unit-(res*3), activation='relu')(layer)
  output = layers.Dense(units=100, activation='softmax')(layer)

  # creamos el modelo
  model = Model(inputs=input, outputs=output)

  # optimizador
  optimizer = optimizer = SGD(learning_rate=0.01)

  # funcin loss
  loss = SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=False)

  # mtrica
  metrics = ['accuracy']

  # compilamos el modelo
  model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss=loss, metrics=metrics)

  # entrenamos
  history = model.fit(x=X_train, y=y_train, batch_size=250, epochs=10,
                              validation_data=(X_validation, y_validation))

  list_val_accuracy.append(history.history['val_accuracy'][-1])
